{"TopicId":198234,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"need RCS prograde retrograde switch","CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-20T21:20:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-20T21:20:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehi, in short: I need a switch between \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003Eprograde and retrograde in a probe that has \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E as the unique propulsion.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Emore in detail: the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E prograde \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003Enozzle is too close to another part of the probe, \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Eprecisely the \u0022Rockomax Brand Adapter 02\u0022.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI don\u0027t know what distance the gas \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Esprinkle \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Eaffects the adapter wasting fuel, but I\u0027m quite sure this one is too much close and it has some effects.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnyway, even if it had no effects, I don\u0027t like to see the expelled gas sprays the adapter.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo, as I have the \u0022opposite direction \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E nozzle\u0022 free from obstacles, I would like to use it instead.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOf course I pretty know I could turn the probe direction anti-target \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:targetretro:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/TargetRetro20px.png\u0022 title=\u0022:targetretro:\u0022\u003E and burn manually, but I want to burn automatically.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat\u0027s why I\u0027m asking, \u003Cstrong\u003Ecan I somehow switch prograde and retrograde \u0022properties\u0022 in order to execute a maneuver with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E but using the opposite nozzle?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bad.jpg?dl=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/fjr54cxf1ay7qur/bad.jpg?dl=1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022good.jpg?dl=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/vzy4gu66cne3x8t/good.jpg?dl=1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried to switch the \u0022Control Point = Reversed\u0022 instead of Default in the Pod settings, but no changes. I don\u0027t even know what does it do.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Eand since I\u0027m here: \u003Cstrong\u003Ewhat does \u0022Control Point\u0022 do when \u0022Reversed\u0022?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022control%20point%20reversed.jpg?dl=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002282.08\u0022 height=\u0022751\u0022 width=\u0022915\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/4unx2atuplimxy6/control%20point%20reversed.jpg?dl=1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-20T21:44:02Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2020 09:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-20T21:24:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mod by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E which will let you do this,I dont remember the name right now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-20T21:27:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605907483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mod by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E which will let you do this,I dont remember the name right now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, waiting for the \u0022Tardigrade\u0022. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-20T21:32:04Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2020 09:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-20T23:37:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884191\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605907641\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, waiting for the \u0022Tardigrade\u0022. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1867237315\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/180725-110-attitudeadjuster-v12-set-control-point-via-action-group-variable-pitch-control-point-for-spaceplane-reentry/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-20T23:37:53Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2020 11:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T00:18:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605907250\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, even if it had no effects, I don\u0027t like to see the expelled gas sprays the adapter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can pretend to not see the spray, since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrust don\u0027t get occluded. (They may still get stowed inside a fairing/cargo bay) .\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want the thrust to respond to throttle you need to [show activation toggles] and set [fore by throttle] on. (Requires advanced tweakables). \u0022fore\u0022 being were your craft is pointing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605907250\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat does \u0022Control Point\u0022 do when \u0022Reversed\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly what it says: Up becomes Down, Left becomes Right, etc.. Just look at the Navball and you will notice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T01:16:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884185\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605907250\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried to switch the \u0022Control Point = Reversed\u0022 instead of Default in the Pod settings, but no changes. I don\u0027t even know what does it do.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Eand since I\u0027m here: \u003Cstrong\u003Ewhat does \u0022Control Point\u0022 do when \u0022Reversed\u0022?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit should do exactly what you want to achieve: prograde becomes retrograde, and everything else is changed accordingly. should satisfy your need to trick the game into burning in the opposite direction\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T02:54:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605917898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly what it says: Up becomes Down, Left becomes Right, etc.. Just look at the Navball and you will notice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605921362\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit should do exactly what you want to achieve: prograde becomes retrograde, and everything else is changed accordingly. should satisfy your need to trick the game into burning in the opposite direction\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI tried it reversed only on a probe, that\u0027s why I said there was no changes, when I tried it on the main ship it worked.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003ESo what prevents it to operate on the probes where I need it?\u003Cbr\u003E\nVideo: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/yzn9xzsw2sjotk8/2020-11-21%2003-41-59.mkv?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/yzn9xzsw2sjotk8/2020-11-21 03-41-59.mkv?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nedit:\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf I press \u0022Control from here\u0022 the probe start rotating according to \u0022Control Point: Reversed\u0022 but it never burns. why?\u003Cbr\u003E\nVideo: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/f0gotu98lr7gt56/2020-11-21%2004-42-05.mkv?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/f0gotu98lr7gt56/2020-11-21 04-42-05.mkv?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-21T04:41:15Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2020 04:41  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T05:35:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605917898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsince \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrust don\u0027t get occluded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I just made a test vessel, you\u0027re right: \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters don\u0027t get occluded.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut I\u0027m sure about other fuel engines, they get occluded.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI remember long time ago I built a lander and one of its Nerv engines was occluded by an extended solar panel 1x6, or by a radiator.\u003Cbr\u003E\nResulting in a crash due to unbalanced symmetric thrust while landing.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nStill don\u0027t know why that probe \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003Edoes not want to burn when its \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003EControl Point is Reversed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-21T13:38:44Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2020 01:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T08:55:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605927261\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what prevents it to operate on the probes where I need it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe control point (\u0022Control from here\u0022) wasn\u0027t set to that probe core. (IIRC it can be that after decoupling the control point is set to a non probe core / cockpit / docking port part.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T13:25:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605948937\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe control point (\u0022Control from here\u0022) wasn\u0027t set to that probe core. (IIRC it can be that after decoupling the control point is set to a non probe core / cockpit / docking port part.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes thanks, \u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan title=\u0022\u0022\u003EI had already figured out it.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605927261\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit:\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf I press \u0022Control from here\u0022 the probe start rotating according to \u0022Control Point: Reversed\u0022 but it never burns. why?\u003Cbr\u003E\nVideo: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/f0gotu98lr7gt56/2020-11-21%2004-42-05.mkv?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/f0gotu98lr7gt56/2020-11-21 04-42-05.mkv?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhat I still do not know is why the probe do not burns when is reversed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-21T13:55:22Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2020 01:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by antipro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T14:30:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884437\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605965106\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022antipro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, antipro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I still do not know is why the probe do not burns when is reversed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is that this is a feature of MechJeb or another mod. Something sets the throttle to zero when you activate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E, that\u0027s not stock behavior.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"antipro","CreatedById":173370,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-21T14:39:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223884450\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198234\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221605969020\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is that this is a feature of MechJeb or another mod. Something sets the throttle to zero when you activate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, that\u0027s not stock behavior.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nindeed, I suppose it\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E, but did not find a related option yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}